{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778273196,"nonce":"/u1tSp7RhYL6RXVBtNjHUuL8X1U=","message":"**Stage 0 effectively complete** (pending merge): the recipe-bug audit at `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/cs_alignment_audit.md` traced the analytical-Δv ceiling at +2.12% (initial implementation in `1f75d9f`, `1c313b4`) to **five recipe-level bugs in the C\u0026S-faithful builder**, not the structural lift itself.\n\nThe five bugs:\n1. `_apply_delay_augmentation` zero-padded Q on the lag block instead of distributing per `AugRobustControl.m` (`1/(h+1)` weight per block, time-shifted Qaug). The lag chain was UNREACHABLE from u, UNDISTURBED by w, and UNCOSTED by Q, so the H∞ Riccati found `P[lag, lag] = 0` identically — lag states recorded history with no incentive to react.\n2. The lag chain tracked the observation channel (`n_obs = 4`: pos + vel) instead of the full physical state (`n = 8`) per `AugRobustControl.m` line 24.\n3. `cs_eq15_cost_schedule(state_dim=8)` zero-padded entries 6,7 (integrators) and ramped *all* eight diagonal entries by `(t/N)^6`. The MATLAB code at `script_minmax_pointMass.m` line 30 ramps only entries 0-3 (pos, vel) and keeps entries 4-7 (force, integrator) at constant 1.\n4. The ramp denominator was `T` instead of matching MATLAB's `(i*delta/time)^6` with `time/delta` ratio (60 for nStep=60), and the cap `min(1, ...)` was missing.\n5. Default `tau = 0.06` instead of C\u0026S's `tau = 0.066` (`minmaxfc_pointMass.m` line 23).\n\nCombined effect: the augmentation was mathematically inert and Δv stuck at +2.12% (identical to the legacy 6-state form). After fixing all five (commits `215a06a`, `02cfdf7`, `e1cd78e` on `feature/cs-faithful-8state-delay`), the canonical 15 cm reach Δv reaches **+8.31% at γ_des → γ\\*** and +7.49% at γ_des = 1.05γ\\*, matching the MATLAB-faithful Python port (+8.24% at γ\\*, see `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/cs_alignment/cs_matlab_port.py`) within ~0.1pp and the user-measured Fig 1e ~+7.76%. K_phys block matches the MATLAB port to ~9% relative error under matched discretisation (FE).\n\nThe new public API exposes `apply_delay_distribution_to_schedule(schedule, delay_steps, n_phys)` so callers build the *physical* Q schedule via `cs_eq15_cost_schedule(state_dim=8)` and then distribute across the lag chain. Tests updated, MATLAB-port equivalence test added (`test_cs_canonical_dv_matches_matlab_port`).\n\nSynthesis correction lives on `feature/synthesis-cs-target-reframe` (commit `5555e06`).","files":null}]}